                 Read Me


*******************************************************
*  Problem description
*******************************************************

Create a socket that implements stop and wait protocol
and analyze the RTT for varying message sizes.

*******************************************************
*  Source files
*******************************************************

Name:  sender.c
   Client side.

Name: reciever.c
   Server side.

*******************************************************
*  Circumstances of programs
*******************************************************

   This program works and runs as intended.

   Simulates Stop-and-wait ARQ.
  
   The program was tested on :
	gcc version: 10.1.0

*******************************************************
*  How to build and run the program
*******************************************************

1. Run the sender side (from another terminal window):
   gcc sender.c -o sender
   ./sender

2. Run the reciever side (from another terminal window):
   gcc reciever.c -o reciever
   ./reciever
